Pre-Game Insights: The Philadelphia 76ers have been in decent shape as they've won six of their last nine games overall, but they will be hoping to avoid a third straight defeat after getting scorched by the Warriors in a 139-105 road defeat on Thursday.
Joel Embiid led the team with 28 points and 14 rebounds, Paul George added 19 points while Tyrese Maxey chipped in with 14 points, six assists, and four steals.

The Brooklyn Nets have been in a slump as they've lost eight of their last 11 games overall, but they will be eager to build some momentum after sneaking past the Bucks in a thrilling 113-110 road win on Thursday.

Cameron Johnson led the team with 26 points on 10 of 16 shooting, Cam Thomas added 24 points in just 22 minutes off the bench, Nic Claxton tallied 16 points with 11 rebounds while D'Angelo Russell chipped in with 11 points and 12 assists.

The 76ers are still missing Kelly Oubre Jr, and they have Joel Embiid listed as questionable, while the Nets are still missing Cameron Johnson and they have Cam Thomas listed as questionable for this one.
The 76ers were starting to build some momentum before they got embarrassed by the Warriors in their last outing, while the Nets were ice-cold before their surprising win over the Bucks.
